had no discrimination policies

262
00:16:59,453 --> 00:17:02,195
against blacks there
or against anybody else.

263
00:17:02,282 --> 00:17:05,111
Well, he was treated like
a prince whenever he came there.

264
00:17:07,330 --> 00:17:10,377
[Russian announcer
introducing Paul robeson]

265
00:17:10,507 --> 00:17:12,901
He didn't really know
what was going on

266
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:14,511
in the rest of the country.

267
00:17:14,642 --> 00:17:16,557
So his identification with
the Soviet union,

268
00:17:16,644 --> 00:17:18,950
whether he was
an actual communist or not

269
00:17:19,081 --> 00:17:24,086
was unimportant, he was theirs
and he supported them,

270
00:17:24,217 --> 00:17:28,873
in policies,
both political and cultural,

271
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:31,137
and made a big speech
at one point

272
00:17:31,267 --> 00:17:33,269
that no black man
and no black person in america

273
00:17:33,356 --> 00:17:35,228
would ever go to war
against the Soviet union,

274
00:17:35,358 --> 00:17:37,447
which sounded like
he was calling for treason

275
00:17:37,534 --> 00:17:40,668
among the black population
in the United States.

276
00:17:40,798 --> 00:17:42,365
Mr. Davis: The statement he made

277
00:17:42,496 --> 00:17:44,585
about blacks not fighting
against their own interests

278
00:17:44,715 --> 00:17:47,979
was interpreted by a lot to
mean that he was saying to US

279
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:49,807
"you blacks can't fight,

280
00:17:49,938 --> 00:17:52,636
you shouldn't fight
the Russians, no matter what."

281
00:17:52,723 --> 00:17:55,639
Then the powers that be,
meaning j. Edgar hoover,

282
00:17:55,770 --> 00:17:58,903
had to cut down Paul's influence

283
00:17:58,990 --> 00:18:01,732
and they set out
to demolish the man

284
00:18:01,863 --> 00:18:04,518
and they took some heavy bites
out of him.

285
00:18:09,436 --> 00:18:10,785
Newsreel announcer:
Baseball's top hitter

286
00:18:10,872 --> 00:18:12,656
and star second baseman
of the Brooklyn Dodgers,

287
00:18:12,743 --> 00:18:15,572
Jackie Robinson,
comes to bat for uncle Sam

288
00:18:15,659 --> 00:18:17,270
to refute Paul robeson's remark

289
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:20,925
that u.S. Negroes would not
fight in a war against Russia.

290
00:18:21,056 --> 00:18:23,145
I'm on my way to Washington
to testify

291
00:18:23,276 --> 00:18:26,322
before the house unamerican
activities committee.

292
00:18:26,453 --> 00:18:27,889
That's all I can say
at this time,

293
00:18:27,976 --> 00:18:29,673
I'll make further statements
in Washington.

294
00:18:29,804 --> 00:18:31,762
Robinson is the last witness
to testify

295
00:18:31,893 --> 00:18:34,461
concerning the loyalty of
the members of his race and

296
00:18:34,591 --> 00:18:37,855
before the committee he reads
his own prepared statement.

297
00:18:37,986 --> 00:18:39,205
I've been asked to express

298
00:18:39,335 --> 00:18:41,729
my views on Paul robeson's
statements in Paris,

299
00:18:41,859 --> 00:18:45,211
to the effect that American
negroes would refuse to fight

300
00:18:45,341 --> 00:18:49,606
in any war against Russia
because we love Russia so much.

301
00:18:49,693 --> 00:18:53,567
I haven't any comment to make
on that statement,

302
00:18:53,654 --> 00:18:57,048
except that if mister robeson
actually made it,

303
00:18:57,179 --> 00:19:01,401
it sounds very silly to me,
and most negroes and Italians,

304
00:19:01,531 --> 00:19:05,666
and Irish, and Jews, and Swedes,
and slavs and other Americans

305
00:19:05,796 --> 00:19:08,669
would act just as all these
groups did in the last war.

306
00:19:08,799 --> 00:19:11,715
They'd do their best to keep
their country out of war.

307
00:19:11,846 --> 00:19:14,936
If unsuccessful, they'd do
their best to help their country

308
00:19:15,023 --> 00:19:16,851
win the war against Russia,

309
00:19:16,938 --> 00:19:19,506
or any other enemy
that threatened US.

310
00:19:25,773 --> 00:19:31,648
Jackie came into the big leagues
in 1947

311
00:19:31,779 --> 00:19:36,871
and we appreciated,
we loved, and we honored

312
00:19:36,958 --> 00:19:39,308
and were honored by him
and his behavior,

313
00:19:39,439 --> 00:19:43,617
both on the baseball field
and off.

314
00:19:43,747 --> 00:19:46,924
We recognize the tremendous
pressure that was on him.

315
00:19:47,055 --> 00:19:50,363
We recognize that he was
required not to hit back.

316
00:19:50,493 --> 00:19:54,845
We recognize that he had been,
to some degree,

317
00:19:54,932 --> 00:19:57,283
willing to give up his own life

318
00:19:57,413 --> 00:20:00,590
so that baseball and
the people who controlled it

319
00:20:00,721 --> 00:20:04,203
could make a statement
that would open up the doors.

320
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:06,683
So I assume the pressure
was put on Jackie

321
00:20:06,814 --> 00:20:11,253
and there he was
in that symbolic position

322
00:20:11,384 --> 00:20:13,647
and I remember years later,

323
00:20:13,777 --> 00:20:17,955
Jackie himself still carrying
the scar and pain

324
00:20:18,042 --> 00:20:20,131
of having to do that.

325
00:20:20,262 --> 00:20:23,831
And it broke his heart
and it broke our hearts, too.

326
00:20:23,961 --> 00:20:26,007
So the blacks here said

327
00:20:26,137 --> 00:20:27,356
"hey, wait a minute,
wait a minute,"

328
00:20:27,487 --> 00:20:29,576
you know,
the organization people,

329
00:20:29,706 --> 00:20:31,491
"we don't want to get
too close to Paul.

330
00:20:31,621 --> 00:20:35,408
We love him like a brother
but he can be poison to US,

331
00:20:35,538 --> 00:20:37,018
we have more important
things to do,

332
00:20:37,148 --> 00:20:40,456
we're trying to fight to get our
rights to go into restaurants,

333
00:20:40,587 --> 00:20:44,852
to go into housing,
to get jobs on an equal basis,

334
00:20:44,982 --> 00:20:47,898
and Paul robeson is just
muddying the waters

335
00:20:48,029 --> 00:20:50,640
with the talk about
the Soviet union."

336
00:20:50,771 --> 00:20:55,732
And so he was alienated
and isolated from all sides.

337
00:20:55,863 --> 00:21:00,650
If you're looking
to create disunity,

338
00:21:00,781 --> 00:21:05,089
if you're looking to destroy
something that is strong,

339
00:21:05,176 --> 00:21:08,310
and good, and real and needed,

340
00:21:08,441 --> 00:21:11,008
you must go after
the most powerful voice

341
00:21:11,139 --> 00:21:14,621
that articulates that agenda.

342
00:21:14,751 --> 00:21:17,363
No voice was greater
than Paul robeson's

343
00:21:17,493 --> 00:21:21,845
in talking about democracy
and the rights of human beings.

344
00:21:21,976 --> 00:21:24,718
There is one of
the greatest cultural figures

345
00:21:24,805 --> 00:21:26,415
in American history,

346
00:21:26,546 --> 00:21:30,376
and he was banned in effect
from making a living.

347
00:21:30,506 --> 00:21:31,812
Nobody wanted to touch him,

348
00:21:31,899 --> 00:21:33,857
couldn't get a passport
to go to Europe,

349
00:21:33,988 --> 00:21:37,731
his concerts here
were kind of damaged.

350
00:21:37,905 --> 00:21:41,343
