the other day, ♪

351
00:21:41,517 --> 00:21:44,738
♪ I gave him my right hand. ♪

352
00:21:44,912 --> 00:21:48,394
♪ And just as soon
as ever my back was turned, ♪

353
00:21:48,568 --> 00:21:51,788
♪ he scandalized my name. ♪

354
00:21:51,962 --> 00:21:54,008
♪ Now do you call
that a brother? ♪

355
00:21:54,182 --> 00:21:56,097
♪ No, no. ♪

356
00:21:56,271 --> 00:21:57,925
♪ You call that a brother? ♪

357
00:21:58,099 --> 00:22:00,101
♪ No, no. ♪

358
00:22:00,275 --> 00:22:01,972
♪ You call that a brother? ♪

359
00:22:02,146 --> 00:22:03,887
♪ No, no. ♪

360
00:22:04,061 --> 00:22:10,198
♪ Scandalize my name. ♪

361
00:22:17,161 --> 00:22:19,729
In American politics
there's always been a large use

362
00:22:19,816 --> 00:22:27,302
of labels or scare words,
behind which were issues

363
00:22:27,433 --> 00:22:30,044
which were not brought out
into the open.

364
00:22:30,174 --> 00:22:33,787
Now during the first world war
it was anarchists.

365
00:22:33,917 --> 00:22:35,745
By the time of
the second world war,

366
00:22:35,876 --> 00:22:38,879
anarchists no longer seemed
very interesting,

367
00:22:39,009 --> 00:22:41,011
but it was more interesting
to call people communists

368
00:22:41,142 --> 00:22:43,797
because of the rise
of the Soviet union.

369
00:22:43,884 --> 00:22:47,583
If you remember, for the longest
time the majority of power

370
00:22:47,714 --> 00:22:51,674
in congress, the decisive power,

371
00:22:51,761 --> 00:22:53,937
was wielded by,
not the dixiecrats,

372
00:22:54,068 --> 00:22:57,376
but the southern component.

373
00:22:57,506 --> 00:22:59,769
Their power rested
entirely on the fact

374
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:02,555
that they represented districts
where blacks could not vote

375
00:23:02,685 --> 00:23:05,993
in which blacks
were in a majority.

376
00:23:06,123 --> 00:23:08,691
So if the blacks won the vote,

377
00:23:08,822 --> 00:23:11,346
their power would end
immediately.

378
00:23:11,477 --> 00:23:14,088
And they were the ones who were
most ardent in their pursuit

379
00:23:14,218 --> 00:23:15,872
of the red devils,
and they were the ones

380
00:23:16,003 --> 00:23:18,484
who were most ardent
in keeping the blacks down.

381
00:23:18,614 --> 00:23:21,661
We know that to j. Edgar hoover,

382
00:23:21,791 --> 00:23:25,055
an interest in improving
the status of the negro

383
00:23:25,186 --> 00:23:28,537
was a communist symptom.

384
00:23:28,668 --> 00:23:31,932
Just as the idea of being
interested in better relations

385
00:23:32,019 --> 00:23:34,674
with the Soviet union
was a communist symptom.

386
00:23:34,761 --> 00:23:36,502
Announcer:
In recognizing a communist,

387
00:23:36,632 --> 00:23:39,243
physical appearance
counts for nothing.

388
00:23:39,330 --> 00:23:42,159
If a person consistently
reads and advocates the views

389
00:23:42,246 --> 00:23:45,467
expressed in
a communist publication,

390
00:23:45,598 --> 00:23:47,730
he may be a communist.

391
00:23:47,861 --> 00:23:52,387
Before McCarthy came along,
the industry,

392
00:23:52,474 --> 00:23:55,521
both Hollywood
and broadcasting,

393
00:23:55,651 --> 00:24:01,004
had already established what
McCarthy was accused of doing,

394
00:24:01,135 --> 00:24:05,052
of sort of terrorizing
the people who worked in it.

395
00:24:05,182 --> 00:24:08,185
I can remember very well
when I first saw "red channels"

396
00:24:08,316 --> 00:24:11,101
because it was my 42nd birthday
and I happened to wander

397
00:24:11,232 --> 00:24:16,150
into a bookstore
and there was this thing,

398
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:20,720
"red channels" with a microphone
and a red hand over it,

399
00:24:20,807 --> 00:24:24,724
and I picked it up to look
at it, it was one dollar,

400
00:24:24,811 --> 00:24:28,249
and I suddenly saw
what it was purported to be,

401
00:24:28,336 --> 00:24:30,207
a documentation of a conspiracy

402
00:24:30,338 --> 00:24:35,212
to take over the broadcast media
for the Soviet cause.

403
00:24:35,343 --> 00:24:39,521
That's what it said it was, and
this was a list of 151 people

404
00:24:39,608 --> 00:24:43,264
that showed who
the conspirators were.

405
00:24:43,394 --> 00:24:45,614
The point of this book was
everything you wanted to know

406
00:24:45,745 --> 00:24:48,312
about every writer or performer

407
00:24:48,443 --> 00:24:51,577
and most of these people
were well known performers

408
00:24:51,664 --> 00:24:53,840
who had appeared at functions
during the war

409
00:24:53,927 --> 00:24:56,930
that had been supported
by the war departments

410
00:24:57,060 --> 00:25:00,586
and Mrs. Roosevelt,
who herself was suspect.

411
00:25:00,673 --> 00:25:04,415
What they are being
condemned for was all the things

412
00:25:04,546 --> 00:25:07,984
that had been liberal impulses
over the last 20 years.

413
00:25:08,115 --> 00:25:12,032
More rights for the negro,
civil liberties,

414
00:25:12,119 --> 00:25:16,036
better relations with
the Soviet union, peace.

415
00:25:16,166 --> 00:25:18,255
"Red channels" was
the beginning of it,

416
00:25:18,386 --> 00:25:20,301
but this was such
a nice business

417
00:25:20,431 --> 00:25:23,870
that other agencies grew up
and did the same sort of thing.

418
00:25:23,957 --> 00:25:25,828
There was an organization
called "aware,"

419
00:25:25,915 --> 00:25:28,614
which very aggressively began
to list other people

420
00:25:28,744 --> 00:25:30,398
who were not in "red channels."

421
00:25:30,485 --> 00:25:34,141
There was a publication
called "counter attack."

422
00:25:34,271 --> 00:25:36,360
There was one called "aware,"

423
00:25:36,491 --> 00:25:38,232
and then there was
the Attorney General

424
00:25:38,362 --> 00:25:41,322
of the United States of America,
who had his own list.

425
00:25:41,452 --> 00:25:43,324
The state department had a list.

426
00:25:43,454 --> 00:25:46,414
J. Edgar hoover and the FBI
had a list.

427
00:25:46,501 --> 00:25:48,895
The ku klux klan had a list,

428
00:25:48,982 --> 00:25:51,724
all the white citizen's groups
had a list.

429
00:25:51,854 --> 00:25:54,074
Some unions had a list.

430
00:25:54,204 --> 00:25:57,556
You had these clearance bodies
set up by some group

431
00:25:57,686 --> 00:26:00,776
that decided,
since they had the expertise,

432
00:26:00,907 --> 00:26:04,432
they could read newspapers
and clip the daily worker

433
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:09,785
and find out who appeared
at a certain kind of function

434
00:26:09,872 --> 00:26:13,702
as a singer, as a writer,
as a performer.

435
00:26:13,833 --> 00:26:15,748
Before you knew it,
some of the best people

436
00:26:15,878 --> 00:26:17,967
in the business
were being blacklisted.

437
00:26:18,141 --> 00:26:33,417
♪

438
00:26:35,158 --> 00:26:39,119
Throughout the 1940s,
something which could be used

439
00:26:39,249 --> 00:26:42,992
against my mother
and many others

440
00:26:43,079 --> 00:26:49,129
was the assertion that
the causes that they embraced

441
00:26:49,259 --> 00:26:52,698
were also causes that
the communist party embraced.

442
00:26:52,828 --> 00:26:55,352
When my mother was confronted
with this, she said

443
00:26:55,483 --> 00:26:59,748
"I'm not going to relax
my efforts to get equal rights

444
00:26:59,879 --> 00:27:02,359
for people of color
merely because

445
00:27:02,446 --> 00:27:05,536
the communist party
also embraces that effort."

446
00:27:05,667 --> 00:27:11,934
And she rejected as totally
false any attempt to claim

447
00:27:12,065 --> 00:27:14,850
that she was a communist
or communist sympathizer

448
00:27:14,937 --> 00:27:17,766
because of her work
for civil rights.

449
00:27:17,853 --> 00:27:20,726
One of the criticisms of her

450
00:27:20,813 --> 00:27:24,730
was that she had entertained
Soviet troops.

451
00:27:24,860 --> 00:27:28,647
"There you are, entertaining
troops of our enemy."

452
00:27:28,734 --> 00:27:30,474
I remember a reporter
asking her about this.

453
00:27:30,605 --> 00:27:32,172
"Miss Scott,

454
00:27:32,302 --> 00:27:34,478
how could you have entertained
these troops of our enemies?"

455
00:27:34,609 --> 00:27:36,306
And she said
"well, look at the date.

456
00:27:36,437 --> 00:27:40,746
It was 1943 and if you recall
we were their allies then."

457
00:27:40,876 --> 00:27:43,400
She did a great deal
of entertaining of troops and

458
00:27:43,531 --> 00:27:46,752
quite often you had joint forces
toward the end of the war,

459
00:27:46,882 --> 00:27:50,103
so she thought it was
no small irony

460
00:27:50,233 --> 00:27:53,933
that she was accused of being
unpatriotic for something which

461
00:27:54,063 --> 00:27:56,762
five years earlier had been
the height of patriotism.

462
00:27:56,849 --> 00:27:58,285
And at the same time,

463
00:27:58,415 --> 00:28:02,376
she was married to a very
controversial member of congress

464
00:28:02,463 --> 00:28:04,857
who himself was the object
of attacks

465
00:28:04,987 --> 00:28:08,164
by some of his colleagues
and others.

466
00:28:08,295 --> 00:28:14,518
She was convinced that
his enemies also had used her

467
00:28:14,605 --> 00:28:16,869
as a way to reach him and that
she was particularly vulnerable

468
00:28:16,999 --> 00:28:20,786
because of the fact
that her livelihood

469
00:28:20,916 --> 00:28:22,657
depended on acceptance,

470
00:28:22,744 --> 00:28:25,791
not only by the public,
who are buying the tickets

471
00:28:25,921 --> 00:28:28,315
and turning on her radio show
and television show,

472
00:28:28,445 --> 00:28:32,623
but also by the networks
and the advertisers.

473
00:28:32,711 --> 00:28:36,366
An atmosphere of mystery
hung over the whole business

474
00:28:36,453 --> 00:28:38,978
of "red channels."

475
00:28:39,108 --> 00:28:42,285
The copies disappeared
into the desks of executives

476
00:28:42,416 --> 00:28:44,505
and they began to use them

477
00:28:44,635 --> 00:28:47,029
to decide whether
or not to hire an actor.

478
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:50,816
One of the themes
of my mother's appearance

479
00:28:50,903 --> 00:28:53,557
before the unamerican
activities committee

480
00:28:53,688 --> 00:28:56,909
was her repeated denials
of the truth

481
00:28:57,039 --> 00:28:58,475
of what had been published.

482
00:28:58,606 --> 00:29:00,042
She said "this is not true"

483
00:29:00,173 --> 00:29:04,612
and it was improper
for a publisher

484
00:29:04,743 --> 00:29:06,832
to in effect try to
end someone's career

485
00:29:06,962 --> 00:29:09,225
by publishing inaccurate
information.

486
00:29:09,356 --> 00:29:11,445
My mother kept pointing out
that at no time had anyone

487
00:29:11,575 --> 00:29:13,839
made a single
telephone call to her,

488
00:29:13,969 --> 00:29:15,449
sent a telegram to her,

